# Moon & Planes Forecast Lens Implementation Plan

## Overview

Implement a unified zone-based knowledge system for moons and planes that mirrors the weather forecast lens structure. The core mechanic is **timing uncertainty** — at range, players know an event is coming but not exactly when. As the event approaches (slides through zones), the window tightens until it resolves to exact dates.

This plan also flags dead code found during investigation.

-----

## Part 1: Unified Zone System (Shared Across All Subsystems)

Same four zones everywhere. Weather uses days, moons and planes use months (~28 days each in Eberron’s 336-day year):

|Zone|Weather      |Moons & Planes         |
|----|-------------|-----------------------|
|A   |Day 1 (today)|Month 1 (~28 days)     |
|B   |Days 2–3     |Months 2–3 (~84 days)  |
|C   |Days 4–6     |Months 4–6 (~168 days) |
|D   |Days 7–10    |Months 7–10 (~280 days)|

Same DC ladder: A = DC 10, B = DC 15, C = DC 20, D = DC 25.
Same tail mechanics (A′ + B′ extending up to 2 more zones past edge).
Same quality ladder and upgrade-only rules.

### Zone determination for moons/planes

```typescript
function _monthZone(serial: number, today: number, yearDays: number): 'A' | 'B' | 'C' | 'D' | null {
  var monthLength = Math.max(1, Math.round(yearDays / 12));
  var dist = serial - today;
  if (dist < 0) return null; // past
  if (dist < monthLength)     return 'A';  // this month
  if (dist < monthLength * 3) return 'B';  // months 2-3
  if (dist < monthLength * 6) return 'C';  // months 4-6
  if (dist < monthLength * 10) return 'D'; // months 7-10
  return null; // beyond display window
}
```

