## Part 5: Cross-Subsystem Synergy (Planes → Weather Lens)

As established in the weather forecast lens plan: if a player has planar knowledge covering a given serial (even with timing uncertainty from a generated event), the weather forecast lens treats the planar weather delta as “known” — exempt from regression.

Keep it simple: any planar reveal that covers the serial (even if the generated event’s uncertainty window merely includes that serial) counts. Don’t try to pro-rate the knowledge based on how confident the planar timing is.

This means:

- Annual canonical planar knowledge (always known at low tier) always informs weather forecasts. Lamannia coterminous in Olarune? Weather lens knows about the precipitation bump.
- Non-annual canonical knowledge (medium+ tier) informs weather when revealed. Fernia coterminous in Lharvion every 5 years? If they have medium planar knowledge, weather lens accounts for the heat.
- Generated events (medium with uncertainty, or high exact) inform weather when the uncertainty window covers the date in question.

