## Part 6: Storage Model

### Moon Reveals — Restructure from Global to Per-Event

The current system stores a single global `revealTier` + `revealHorizonDays`. This must change to per-serial reveal flags (like weather) to support zone-based auto-sharpening and tail mechanics.

New storage structure on moon state:

```typescript
moonReveals: {
  // serial (string) -> reveal entry
  [serial: string]: {
    tier: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high',
    source: 'common' | 'skilled' | 'expert',
    quality: number,  // rank on the quality ladder (1-8)
    isTail: boolean
  }
}
```

On day advance, grant common knowledge (low, zone A quality) for all events within zone A (~28 days). Upgrade-only.

When GM runs `!cal moon send medium 3m`, iterate over all full/new events within 3 months. Tag each with the appropriate quality based on which zone it falls in. Plant A′/B′ tail flags on events in the next 2 months past the edge.

### Planes Reveals — Similar Restructure

Current global `revealTier` + `revealHorizonDays` + `generatedHorizonDays` should be restructured similarly. However, since canonical events are either “always known” (annual) or “known once you have the tier” (non-annual), the per-serial flags mainly matter for:

1. Tracking which generated events have been revealed
1. Tracking quality rank for generated events (zone-based uncertainty)
1. Supporting tail mechanics
1. Supporting auto-sharpening

Canonical events can use a simpler flag: `{ tier: 'medium', source: 'skilled' }` for all dates within the horizon when non-annual canon is revealed. No zone-based quality needed since canonical timing is exact at medium+.

New storage on planes state:

```typescript
planarReveals: {
  canonTier: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high',        // overall canon knowledge level
  canonHorizonDays: number,                      // how far canon knowledge extends
  generatedReveals: {
    // serial (string) -> reveal entry (only for generated events)
    [serial: string]: {
      tier: 'medium' | 'high',
      source: 'skilled' | 'expert',
      quality: number,
      isTail: boolean
    }
  }
}
```

