## Part 12: Edge Cases

1. **Events straddling zone boundaries**: If a multi-day phase (e.g., Aryth full moon spanning 10 days) starts in one zone and ends in another, use the zone of the phase’s **peak day** (the serial stored in the sequence) for uncertainty calculation. The entire phase window shifts together.
1. **Overlapping uncertainty windows**: At zone D, slow moons like Vult might have full and new moon windows that visually overlap. This is acceptable — the player sees “something happening with Vult in this range” and can’t distinguish full from new at that distance. As zones sharpen, they separate.
1. **Uncertainty window extending past the display horizon**: Clamp the rendered window to the 10-month display cap. If an event is near the edge and its uncertainty window extends beyond, show what fits and add “…” or a similar indicator.
1. **First-day fallback**: If no prior event data exists for offset calculation, use a default offset ratio of 0.5 (centered). This only matters on the very first day of a campaign.
1. **Multiple GM anchors close together**: The smoothing algorithm already handles this — each anchor smoothes independently, and the sequence is re-sorted after all anchors are applied. The variable smoothing cycles won’t change this behavior.
1. **Non-Eberron settings**: Settings with 1-3 moons and regular periods (Selûne, Luna/Celene, Solinari/Lunitari/Nuitari, etc.) get the same zone system. The uncertainty windows will be small (since the periods are short/regular) and the system works cleanly. No special-casing needed. Non-Eberron settings have no planes subsystem, so the planes portion is Eberron-only (as it already is).
1. **Annual canonical events at low tier — predictive display**: Low tier should show annual canonical events on the calendar for the full year (not just zone A). These are “holidays” — everyone knows when Lamannia goes coterminous in Olarune. The zone system governs the reveal horizon for medium/high tier non-annual and generated events, but annual canonical events bypass it entirely at all tiers.

